race.comment: CASUAL GHAI (2) did enough first up at Mornington in a slowly run race, covering ground there in a solid effort. He'll be fitter for that and did take on some handy races last time in. REGAL GENT (16) has been good in two runs to date, tackling a metro race at Sandown Hillside last time when boxing on well for sixth. This looks a suitable race from a nice gate. HEIWANA TAMASHI (3) resumes. He got over a bit of ground last time in, last seen running in a Listed race over 1600m at Flemington, finishing fifth there. Tough draw but has the ability to figure. SKYDREAM (13) debuts. Is a half sister to the well performed Hong Kong sprinter Telecom Power. Has done enough at the trials to indicate ablity.
